To get a picture of how dire the situation is, eNCA senior reporter, Siphamandla Goge speaks to Masego Rahlaga from the Polish capital. Courtesy #DStv403 WARSAW - As the fighting between Russia and Ukraine persists, Ukrainians continue to flock to neighbouring Poland in search of safety. The exodus has been described as the largest refugee movement in Europe since the end of World War Two. To get a picture of how dire the situation is, eNCA senior reporter, Siphamandla Goge shares more details from the Polish capital in the video above.